    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">In the Mesilla Valley, rock isn't a compromise — it's the smart move. Gravel and decorative stone don't need water, don't blow away in our spring winds the way mulch does, and won't decompose in the summer heat. A properly installed rock landscape holds its look for years with almost zero upkeep.</p>
